	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=6210&mid=99302956581404>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=6210&mid=99302956581404>RE: DRuids</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=6210&mid=99302956581404#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jun 20th 5:32 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=44737><span id= >Kione</span></a><br><span id=notbold>151 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.23]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Because to properly heal and Damage Shield, you have to target your party members, which means you're not going to be attacking.&nbsp;&nbsp;Basically, at the level at which you can get this, the sharp disparity in skill will make all the difference in the world.  Skill decides how often you hit, and how hard.  Since Druids have a level cap much lower than melee classes, we do a lot less damage meleeing.  Not only that, but the time you're spending inflicting small amounts of damage on the creature could be better spent medding, so you can inflict large amounts of damage on the creature.  Even a weapon like this is not going to measure up to one of our DoTs (at that level,) or even come close to a chain casting of a DD.<br><br>Its not only with grouping, either.  Soloing our damage output is a small fraction compared to the monster's, so you just plain *can't* take more than a handful of hits over the course of the combat.  Soloing essentially means keeping away from the monster.  Heck, at the level I'm at (42) I only melee to finish a monster off once its running, and even then its more efficient to DoT it then med.<br><br>Unfortunetely, after 30 or so, the only classes that really should be meleeing are the actual melee classes.  Everyone else would best serve their groups medding in between spells.  Sure, its cool that a druid can use it, but frankly, you'd be better off with something with Wisdom on it.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
